abstract: >
  HPCSeries Core is a CPU-optimized statistical computing library designed for
  massive datasets (10M+ records). It provides 2-100x faster operations than
  NumPy/Pandas through SIMD vectorization (AVX2/AVX-512 on x86, NEON on ARM),
  OpenMP parallelization, and cache-friendly algorithms. The library features
  architecture-aware compilation that automatically optimizes for Intel Sapphire
  Rapids, Ice Lake, AMD EPYC Genoa, and ARM Graviton3 processors. Version 0.7.0
  introduces comprehensive performance validation across cloud platforms, proving
  memory bandwidth saturation at 2 threads regardless of vCPU countâ€”a hallmark
  of optimal SIMD implementation.
